column5: There a couple of houses on other side.Pretty nice.On the other side of the dam all the way out to outlet bay there are beautifull homes on both sides.Pretty nice boat ride.Guessing 5 miles to Eagle Lake.
No water being let out for a while now.Only water coming out is through turbine..Most lakes are pretty low already.Definatly not as much snow as last year.
Good afternoon,drove through here today and just had a outdoorsy look.Thought I'd share
That's a great pic,wish I was standing by the water when you snapped it.
Lot of pike and walleye make there way up there.
Wouldn't mind at all giving them alittle snack on there way up there.
Very pretty. I don’t envy your winter temps and snow up there but I do the scenery that’s for sure.

So this river goes 3+ miles from this spot and then joins into the Wabigoon River from there to hwy 105.Ive had a boat in there and would say the fishing is very good.Lots of current and 2 sets of rapids with awesome fishing.Not much fishing goes on there.10 miles of river.like a flyout.
Don't need the prov for that water,hiking boots would do the job.

[QUOTE=Eckohlt;6704689]By dam in spring walleyes spawn right there I know guy on hwy 105 who has land on east side of hwy and I would put my deep/wide 14 ft misty river in off his prop.Deep many years moose hunt until the secret was out But did have great fishing.
How nice it would be to have a cabin there and a warm fire burning
Pro nice picture but I cant tell how much water they are letting out. A few weeks ago when we were there it wasn't a lot. Hope that still the case. Please keep the pictures coming.
